.TH "LIGHTNING-NODE-CLOSE-ALL" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-node-close-all \- close all channels
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning node-close-all
.RB [ --force ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Issues a mutual close request for every open channel.
Use
.B --force
for unilateral close (on-chain, slower and more expensive).
.PP
Output:
.nf
{"closed":["channel_id",...], "errors":["channel_id: msg",...]}
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-channel-close (1),
.BR lightning-channel-list (1)
